To Staci Hill,<br><br>
You understand more than you realize.  I had two daughters when I went to Vietnam in 1969.  My third daughter was born a few months after I arrived in Vietnam.  I thank God that I returned to them safely and unharmed - much more fortunate than many.  The strongest lesson I received from the experience was that my family is the most important thing I have - my wife, 3 lovely daugters, and now 4 grandchildren.  I was a 'daddy' when I returned and am now a happy, loving 'PaPa' to grandchildren about the ages of my daughters when I returned.  Your love for your father is obvious.  He can still be your 'daddy'.
<p><code>-- merkleg@texas.net  (Gil Merkle) </code><p>


